HEADWORD: Elatrometer
<hw>El`a*trom"e*ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ a
driver + <ets>-meter</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Physics)</fld> <def>An
instrument for measuring the degree of rarefaction of air contained in
the receiver of an air pump.</def> <altsp>[Spelt also
<asp>elaterometer</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

